    slug: "surahs-to-seek-refuge",
    description: `Surahs to Seek Refuge is a focused Islamic publication that presents the specific chapters of the Holy Quran known as the "seeking refuge" surahs — Surah al-Falaq (Chapter 113) and Surah an-Nas (Chapter 114) — along with Surah al-Ikhlas (Chapter 112), which is traditionally recited alongside them for protection and spiritual fortification. These three short but immensely powerful surahs form the concluding chapters of the Quran and are among the most frequently recited portions of the scripture in the daily life of Muslims. The book provides the complete Arabic text of these surahs with vowel marks (tashkeel) for correct pronunciation, accompanied by translations and explanatory notes that illuminate their meaning and significance.

The book begins with an introduction to the concept of seeking refuge (isti'adhah) in Islam, explaining the Quranic command to seek refuge in Allah from the various forms of evil and harm that can afflict human beings. The author discusses the different categories of evil mentioned in these surahs — the evil of external forces such as dark magic and envy (addressed in Surah al-Falaq), and the evil of internal whisperings and temptations (addressed in Surah an-Nas) — and explains how the combined recitation of these surahs provides comprehensive spiritual protection. The commentary draws upon the classical tafsir works, including Ibn Kathir, at-Tabari, and as-Sa'di, to provide a thorough understanding of each verse.

For Surah al-Ikhlas, the book explains how this surah encapsulates the essence of monotheism (tawheed) by affirming Allah's absolute oneness, His self-sufficiency, His freedom from any physical or conceptual limitations, and His uniqueness in all His attributes. The author explains the hadith that describes Surah al-Ikhlas as being equivalent to one-third of the Quran in its meaning and significance, highlighting the central role that tawheed plays in the Islamic faith. The practical section of the book provides guidance on when and how these surahs should be recited according to the prophetic Sunnah — including the morning and evening adhkar, before sleeping, during illness, and in times of fear or difficulty. The book includes the supplications of the Prophet (peace be upon him) that incorporate these surahs, making it a practical manual for spiritual protection. Surahs to Seek Refuge is a valuable resource for Muslims of all ages and backgrounds who want to understand the full meaning and proper application of these essential Quranic chapters.`,
